**The Crossroads**

You emerge from the dense underbrush into a small clearing where three paths diverge. The forest here feels
alive with an ancient presence. A mysterious gray cat sits perched on a weathered stone marker at the center,
its luminous eyes tracking your every movement.

The western path descends into dark woods where shadows seem to move of their own accord. To the east, you can
see the path climbing toward distant mountains, their peaks catching the last rays of daylight. The southern
path disappears into a bank of low-lying mist.

The cat's tail flicks once, twice, then stills. It seems to be waiting.

**What do you do?**

- [ ] Approach the cat and ask for guidance
- [x] Take the eastern path toward the mountains
- [ ] Enter the dark woods to the west
- [ ] Follow the misty southern path

